jobs.title: Data Science Manager
jobs.summary: Net Science is seeking a highly skilled and motivated Data Science Manager to lead our team of data scientists in London, ON. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in machine learning, deep learning, and data visualization, with a passion for deriving insights from complex datasets to drive business decisions.
responsibilities: Lead and manage a team of data scientists, providing mentorship, guidance, and professional development opportunities.
Develop and implement advanced machine learning models and deep learning algorithms to solve complex business problems.
Oversee the design and creation of data visualizations to effectively communicate insights to stakeholders.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate data-driven solutions into existing systems and workflows.
Ensure the accuracy, quality, and reliability of data and models through rigorous testing and validation.
Drive innovation by exploring new technologies and methodologies in the field of data science.
Manage data science projects from conception to deployment, ensuring timely delivery and alignment with business objectives.
qualifications: Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or a related field.
5+ years of experience in data science, with at least 2 years in a managerial role.
Expert proficiency in SQL for database management and data retrieval.
Advanced skills in machine learning and data visualization tools and techniques.
Proven expertise in deep learning and experience with TensorFlow.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to think strategically.
Excellent communication skills to effectively present complex information to non-technical stakeholders.
Experience with R, Tableau, and Pandas is highly desirable.

jobs.title: Data Science Manager

5+ years of experience in data science with a proven track record of managing teams.
Advanced proficiency in R and Pandas for data manipulation and analysis.
Expert-level experience in TensorFlow for developing deep learning models.
Strong understanding of deep learning and machine learning principles.
Experience with SQL for database querying and management.
Intermediate skills in Tableau for data visualization and reporting.

Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple projects simultaneously.
